Peel and grate the ginger. Use a #teaspoon{} to easily scrape away the peel.

Place a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{} over medium-high heat with a
drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When hot, add the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated) and fry until fragrant,
~{1%minute}.

Stir the @jasmine rice{150%g} into the #pot along with 300ml cold salted
@water{300%ml}(salted).

Bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{12%minutes}, then remove the #pot from the heat. Keep
covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue
to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, strip the leafy parts of the @kale{80%g} from the stem. Discard the
stems (they're too tough to eat).

Peel and grate the @garlic{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @chives{5%g}.

Trim the tip of the @broccoli{1}. Cut head into small florets and stem into
2cm pieces.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry @Irish beef mince{250%g} until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break it
up with a #spoon{} as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Mince is cooked
> when no longer pink in the middle.

Add broccoli, kale, garlic, and @sesame seeds{1%sachet} (with a drizzle of oil
if necessary). Fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @teriyaki sauce{1%sachet}, @water{50%ml} and half the
@soy sauce{1%sachet}.

Cover and cook, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @aioli{1%sachet} and remaining soy sauce into a
#small bowl{}.

Mix well to combine.

Taste the sauce and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} if
necessary.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}.

Divide the rice, teriyaki beef mince and sesame veg between #bowls{}.

Drizzle the aioli over the veg.

Garnish the dish with a sprinkling of chives.